      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The snowpack is largely stable and its surface has a melt-freeze crust. <br/> <br/> The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust only at high altitudes and will soften earlier than the day before. <br/> <br/> In particular very steep shady slopes high altitudes: Individual weak layers exist in the centre of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of highly fluctuating temperatures and solar radiation the snowpack will consolidate at the weekend."
